x = 1 + 1/x
x^2 = x + 1

Solving the roots of the equation

x^2 -x -1 = 0

x = -b + underroot(b^2 - 4ac)   = 1 + underroot(1 - 4 * 1 * -1) = 1 + underroot(5)
    --------------------------    -----------------------------   ----------------
             2a                             2 * 1                       2

(fixed-point (lambda(x) (+ 1 (/ 1 x))) 1.0)